From: postmarketOS platina port <macosmojave2@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] ath10k: do not advertise power save on WCN3990 (SDM660)

On the Xiaomi Mi 8 Lite (platina, SDM660) the WCN3990 WLAN firmware
(WLAN.HL.1.0.1.c6), which runs inside the modem subsystem, crashes
(EX:wlan_process, PC=b00c75b8) the instant it receives the WMI set_psmode
command. mac80211 sends that command during vdev setup whenever the driver
advertises SUPPORTS_PS. The crash takes down the MSS remoteproc and aborts any
operation (e.g. the very first scan never runs).

A clean-boot WMI trace shows set_psmode is the sole trigger: every QMI/board/BDF
step succeeds, the firmware is ready, and the crash happens exactly at
"wmi tlv set psmode", before "wmi tlv start scan".

Do not advertise PS for WCN3990 so mac80211 never issues set_psmode, keeping the
device operational. Power save is a power-optimisation, not required for
functional WiFi.

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath10k/mac.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath10k/mac.c
@@ -10064,7 +10064,15 @@
 
 	ieee80211_hw_set(ar->hw, SIGNAL_DBM);
 
-	if (!test_bit(ATH10K_FW_FEATURE_NO_PS,
+	/*
+	 * The WCN3990 WLAN firmware (WLAN.HL.1.0.1.c6) running inside the modem
+	 * on the SDM660 crashes (EX:wlan_process, PC=b00c75b8) the moment it
+	 * receives the WMI set_psmode command that mac80211 triggers when power
+	 * save is advertised. Do not advertise PS for WCN3990 so mac80211 never
+	 * sends set_psmode; this keeps the device operational (scan/connect).
+	 */
+	if (!QCA_REV_WCN3990(ar) &&
+	    !test_bit(ATH10K_FW_FEATURE_NO_PS,
 		      ar->running_fw->fw_file.fw_features)) {
 		ieee80211_hw_set(ar->hw, SUPPORTS_PS);
 		ieee80211_hw_set(ar->hw, SUPPORTS_DYNAMIC_PS);
